      "rationale": "Model construction and execution governed by FDA OSEL SOP-FEA-003 (Rev. 2). Independent analyst reviewed boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions prior to production runs. Discrepancies resolved and documented in model review log."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with nonlinear contact, bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity for Ti-6Al-4V rod. Required Gradation 3: model physics justified by published literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic screw body with nonlinear rod (bilinear kinematic hardening, E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa) and frictional contact (μ=0.2) at all interfaces. Model form supported by published Ti-6Al-4V constitutive data and prior FDA FEA validation studies. Sensitivity analysis confirmed plasticity representation dominates yield force prediction; elastic-only formulation was rejected based on 12% over-prediction."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry, and boundary conditions sourced from manufacturer data sheets and direct measurement of test specimens. Required Gradation 3: inputs traceable to measurements with uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry digitized from manufacturer CAD files and verified against coordinate-measuring machine measurements of production parts (n=5). Ti-6Al-4V rod material properties sourced from tensile coupon testing (n=6, mean ± 1SD reported). UHMWPE block material properties from published ASTM F1717 material specification. Uncertainty in key inputs propagated via Monte Carlo (n=1000) to bound QoI uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Production-representative test specimens from the same manufacturing lot as the device under assessment. Required Gradation 2: specimens traceable to production process.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; all specimens drawn from the same production lot (lot 2019-NC-75). Specimens inspected for dimensional conformance prior to testing. Testing performed across two independent laboratories (FDA OSEL and DePuy Synthes) to assess inter-laboratory variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at minimum two load levels and two fixation configurations. Required Gradation 3: multiple test conditions covering clinical use envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard configuration (45 mm offset, quasi-static ramp to failure). Only one loading condition evaluated; no variation in offset distance, load rate, or fixation configuration was explored. This single-condition approach limits the ability to characterize model behavior across the clinical use envelope and represents a shortfall relative to the required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs matched to test specimen measurements; differences quantified and shown to be within acceptable tolerance. Required Gradation 2: documented input matching.",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs updated to reflect measured specimen geometry and material properties for each of the N=11 constructs where individual measurements were available. Mean measured dimensions used for constructs without individual CMM data. Input equivalency table provided in supplementary documentation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric and percent difference for all three QoIs; acceptance bounds pre-specified. Required Gradation 3: statistical comparison with uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) compared using E/uval metric (Oberkampf and Roy) with pre-specified acceptance bound of E/uval < 1.96. Percent difference also computed; all QoIs within 10% bound. E/uval values: stiffness 0.84, yield force 1.21, force at 40 mm 0.97. All acceptance criteria satisfied."
    },
